POLICE in Tshwane District arrested a 47-year-old suspect in Pretoria Moot on Wednesday, 01 March following a spate of business burglaries and robberies reported in the area. According to Captain Amanda van Wyk, various law enforcement agencies followed up on information about suspects who specifically targeted businesses selling inverters, solar panels and batteries. “The team swiftly responded to a business burglary in progress and a highspeed chase ensued while the suspects threw inverters, batteries and tools out of their vehicle's window along the way,” van Wyk said. ALSO READ: Giant potholes closed! She said the vehicle was intercepted and the suspects tried to flee but the police apprehended one suspect. Van Wyk said the other two managed to evade arrest. “Police recovered lithium batteries, inverters and breaking implements,” she added.